Anyone with a feminist for a mom knows she&rsquo;s given you some of the best life advice you&rsquo;ll ever get.&nbsp;She&rsquo;s a strong woman who makes her opinion known and doesn&rsquo;t take shit from anyone. Whether she&rsquo;s been working a 9 to 5 her entire life or has stayed at home to raise you she&rsquo;s a role model in every way.&nbsp;To celebrate Mother&rsquo;s Day,&nbsp;HuffPost Women asked our readers to share one lesson they&rsquo;ve learned from their feminist mothers growing up. The responses, paraphrased below, were heart-wrenching, honest and full of love.&nbsp;So, for my feminist mom&nbsp;&mdash; and every other mother &mdash; this is for you. Here are 28 things anyone with a feminist mother knows to be true. Happy Mother&rsquo;s Day!&nbsp;1. Always trust your intuition. You&nbsp;did get it from your mama.&nbsp;2. Get a good education so you can support yourself if need be.&nbsp;&nbsp;3. Don&rsquo;t ever accept anything less than equal treatment.&nbsp;4. Exercise your hard-won right to vote.5. Actions really do speak louder than words.6. You can be delicate and strong at the same damn time. &nbsp;7. Self-care is everything.&nbsp;8. Being a strong woman means lifting up other women around you.&nbsp;9. Relationships shouldn&rsquo;t&nbsp;complete&nbsp;your life, they should complement it.&nbsp;10. You don&rsquo;t need to smile for anyone.11. Don&rsquo;t water yourself down to be &ldquo;likable,&rdquo; especially for a partner.&nbsp;12. Gender roles are bullshit.&nbsp;13. Value your intelligence, even when those around you don&rsquo;t.&nbsp;14. Life is about balance; don&rsquo;t ever lose sight of your needs and wants.&nbsp;15. Value diversity and acceptance.&nbsp;16. A sense of humor goes a long way when you&rsquo;re in a society built by and for men. &nbsp;&nbsp;17. Respect and learn from the women who came before you.&nbsp;18. Always maintain an avenue for financial independence.&nbsp;19. Housework is a shared chore.&nbsp;20. You can be a strong independent woman and still live happily ever after.&nbsp;21.&nbsp;Speak your mind.&nbsp;22. No one can validate your self worth except you.&nbsp;23. Compassion is key.&nbsp;24. Do what makes you happy.&nbsp;25. Being a woman does not dictate what you can and cannot do.&nbsp;26. Always negotiate your salary.&nbsp;27. Don&rsquo;t let anyone view you as a body instead of a mind.&nbsp;28. You are always enough.